Package: python3-keylime
Architecture: all
Depends: python3-keylime-server,
         python3-keylime-agent,
         python3-keylime-agent-local,
         python3-keylime-tenant,
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: Keylime - full local install
 ${Description}
 .
 This is a metapackage meant for compatibility with former versions
 and will depend on python3-keylime-tenant, python3-keylime-server and
 python3-keylime-agent as well as python3-keylime-agent-local bringing
 all services onto the local system including a configuration to connect
 against the local services.

Package: python3-keylime-lib
Architecture: all
Depends: libtss2-dev,
         python3,
         python3-alembic,
         python3-cryptography,
         python3-gnupg,
         python3-m2crypto,
         python3-requests,
         python3-simplejson,
         python3-sqlalchemy,
         python3-tornado,
         python3-yaml,
         python3-zmq,
         tpm-udev,
         tpm2-abrmd,
         tpm2-tools,
         ${misc:Depends},
         ${python3:Depends}
Description: Keylime python library
 ${Description}
 .
 These are the python libraries shared by server and agent components.

Package: python3-keylime-server
Architecture: all
Depends: adduser,
         python3-keylime-lib,
         python3,
         ${misc:Depends},
         ${python3:Depends}
Recommends: python3-keylime-tenant
Description: Keylime registrar and verifier
 ${Description}
 .
 These are the services "registrar" and "verifier" which make up a keylime
 management server.

Package: python3-keylime-agent
Architecture: all
Depends: adduser,
         python3-keylime-lib,
         python3,
         ${misc:Depends},
         ${python3:Depends}
Description: Keylime agent
 ${Description}
 .
 This is the keylime agent which is meant to run on all measured/monitored
 systems - it comes without a default configuration and will not start until
 one is provided.
 .
 Once you deploy /etc/keylime-agent.conf via any means the service will
 start using that configuration. There is an /etc/keylime-agent.conf.example
 provided to start with.

Package: python3-keylime-tenant
Architecture: all
Depends: adduser,
         python3-keylime-lib,
         python3,
         ${misc:Depends},
         ${python3:Depends}
Description: Keylime tenant tool
 ${Description}
 .
 A tool for provisioning and to control keylime suite.

Package: python3-keylime-agent-local
Architecture: all
Depends: python3-keylime-agent,
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: Keylime config for a local installation
 ${Description}
 .
 This package contains a default config for running the agent against a local
 verifier/registrar which is useful for testing but not a common real scenario
 for keylime.
